### Register user (use an existing image author username for owner test)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{"username":"chunkylover23","email":"chunkylover23@example.com","password":"password"}

### Register user 400 (missing email and password)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{"username":"x"}

### Register user 409 (username already taken)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{"username":"chunkylover23","email":"chunkylover23@example.com","password":"password"}

### Login user (copy token from response)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/tokens
Content-Type: application/json

{"username":"chunkylover23","password":"password"}

### Login 400 (missing password)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/tokens
Content-Type: application/json

{"username":"chunkylover23"}

### Login 401 (wrong password)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/tokens
Content-Type: application/json

{"username":"chunkylover23","password":"wrong"}

### GET all images 401 (no token)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/images

### GET all images 200 (with token)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/images
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_TOKEN_HERE>

### GET one image 200 (with token)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/images/69ae2ec8e31830e248c0aa0d
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_TOKEN_HERE>

### Rename image 401 (no token)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/69ae2ec8e31830e248c0aa0d
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Renamed by owner"}

### Rename image 204 (owner, with token)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/69ae2ec8e31830e248c0aa0d
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_TOKEN_HERE>
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Renamed by owner"}

### Rename image 403 (not owner, with token)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/69ae2ec8e31830e248c0aa0f
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_TOKEN_HERE>
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Should fail"}